# Forvis Mazars Styling Guide

Professional, corporate styling consistent with Forvis Mazars brand guidelines and existing application patterns.

## Brand Colors

### Primary Palette

```typescript
// Forvis Mazars Blue (Primary Brand Color)
forvis-blue-500: '#2E5AAC'  // Primary - use for CTAs, links, accents
forvis-blue-600: '#25488A'  // Hover states
forvis-blue-700: '#1C3667'  // Active states
forvis-blue-50:  '#EBF2FA'  // Backgrounds, highlights
forvis-blue-100: '#D6E4F5'  // Subtle backgrounds

// Professional Grays
forvis-gray-900: '#212529'  // Headings, primary text
forvis-gray-800: '#343A40'  // Body text
forvis-gray-700: '#495057'  // Secondary text
forvis-gray-600: '#6C757D'  // Muted text
forvis-gray-300: '#DEE2E6'  // Borders
forvis-gray-200: '#E9ECEF'  // Dividers
forvis-gray-100: '#F1F3F5'  // Subtle backgrounds
forvis-gray-50:  '#F8F9FA'  // Page backgrounds
```

### Usage Guidelines

**Primary Blue**: Reserve for interactive elements, links, primary actions
**Grays**: Use for text hierarchy, borders, backgrounds
**White**: Card backgrounds, form inputs, modals

## Typography

### Font Family

```css
font-family: 'Inter', system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', 'Roboto', 'Arial', sans-serif
```

Use Inter for all text. Already configured in globals.css and imported from Google Fonts.

### Text Hierarchy

```typescript
// Headings - always semibold, use forvis-gray-900
h1: 'text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold text-forvis-gray-900'
h2: 'text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-forvis-gray-900'
h3: 'text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold text-forvis-gray-900'
h4: 'text-lg font-semibold text-forvis-gray-900'
h5: 'text-base font-semibold text-forvis-gray-900'

// Body Text
body:         'text-sm text-forvis-gray-800'      // Default body
body-large:   'text-base text-forvis-gray-800'
body-small:   'text-xs text-forvis-gray-800'

// Secondary Text
muted:        'text-sm text-forvis-gray-600'
caption:      'text-xs text-forvis-gray-600'
label:        'text-sm font-medium text-forvis-gray-700'
```

### Font Weights

- **300** (light): Rarely used
- **400** (normal): Body text, paragraphs
- **500** (medium): Labels, emphasized text
- **600** (semibold): Headings, subheadings
- **700** (bold): Strong emphasis
- **800** (extrabold): Rare, special emphasis only

